The paper discusses a deep neural network extension to the traditional canonical correlation analysis (CCA) and proposes a method for stochastic optimization of the deep CCA objective. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions multi-view representation learning, which is a common topic in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions memory consumption, which is a common concern in Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM, ordered from most to least likely.
